data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider deprecated the sync-over-async opt-in. **In .NET 11 (EF Core 11), that opt-in is removed entirely.** All four of your sync calls — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` — will throw `InvalidOperationException` at runtime with no workaround.

### The fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

### Key things to propagate up the call chain

| Sync (broken in .NET 11) | Async replacement |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First()` / `Single()` | `await FirstAsync()` / `await SingleAsync()` |
| `Count()` / `Any()` | `await CountAsync()` / `await AnyAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

**Callers must go async too** — controller actions, service methods, etc. need `async Task<T>` signatures all the way up. ASP.NET Core controllers already support this natively.
